        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 16 at 3:25PM CDT until August 16 at 4:00PM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 325 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Roscoe, moving
southeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Rockton, Shirland, Candlewick Lake, Machesney Park, Caledonia,
Harrison, Loves Park, Roscoe, Rockford, South Beloit, Timberlane,
Durand, and Poplar Grove.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
